{{Infobox person | name = Alexa Andrzejewski | image = Alexa Andrzejewski (4620249889).jpg | alt = Alexa Andrzejewski speaking at Big Omaha 2010 | caption = Andrzejewski speaking at Big Omaha 2010 | birth_name = Alexa Weber | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = American | other_names = | occupation = User experience designer, entrepreneur | years_active = | known_for = Foodspotting | notable_works = }} '''Alexa Andrzejewski''' is an American [[user experience design]]er and [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]]. She is best known as the co-founder and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of Foodspotting, an app that allows users to socially share their food photographs. She was named to [[Inc. (magazine)|''Inc.''<nowiki/>'s]] 2011 list of "[[Inc. 30 under 30|30 Under 30]]" and to [[Forbes|''Forbes''<nowiki/>']] 2012 "[[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]]: Food and Wine" list.
== Biography == Andrzejewski (née Weber) had an interest in technology from a young age, learning to reprogram her childhood computer at eight years old and design websites for local businesses by the time she was in [[Middle school|junior high school]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/3566e886-e32a-11e0-bb55-00144feabdc0|title=Billion dollar brains|last=Dembosky|first=April|date=November 23, 2011|newspaper=Financial Times|access-date=October 4, 2016|issn=0307-1766}} {{subscription required}}</ref>
After graduating from college, Andrzejewski joined a design firm called Adaptive Path in [[San Francisco]], California.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://www.inc.com/30under30/2011/profile-alexa-andrzejewski-soraya-darabi-ted-grubb%2520founders-foodspotting.html|title=Alexa Andrzejewksi, Soraya Darabi, and Ted Grubb, Founders of Foodspotting|last=Lagorio-Chafkin|first=Christine|date=June 27, 2016|website=Inc.|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=October 4, 2016}}</ref> In 2009, Andrzejewski was inspired to launch Foodspotting, an app that allows users to socially share their food photographs, after being unable to find the Japanese dish [[okonomiyaki]] in San Francisco.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2012/02/foodspotting-app-rec-updates/|title=Foodspotting App Adds Dish Recommendations to the Menu|last=Bonnington|first=Christina|date=February 1, 2012|work=Wired|access-date=June 17, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.themuse.com/advice/startup-success-stories-alexa-andrzejewski-of-foodspotting|title=Start-up Success Stories: Alexa Andrzejewski of Foodspotting|last=Vartanian|first=Varci|date=April 5, 2012|website=The Muse|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=October 4, 2016}}</ref> She began the project alongside programmer Ted Grubb and social media strategist Soraya Darabi.<ref name=":3" /> Billed as a "visual guide to food," the app allows users to enter their city and a type of food to get photos showing local restaurants that carry the dish.<ref name=":1" /> Since its launch, the service has been named to [[Time (magazine)|''Time's'']] list of 50 Best Websites of 2010<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2012721_2012915_2012910,00.html|title=50 Best Websites 2010|last=|first=|date=August 25, 2010|newspaper=Time|access-date=October 4, 2016|issn=0040-781X}}</ref> and featured at [[Facebook|Facebook's]] [[Facebook F8|f8]] conference.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/women2/2011/09/23/foodspotting-founder-and-ceo-alexa-andrzejewski-virtually-only-woman-onstage-at-facebook-developer-conference/#1cf2c2db78d4|title=Foodspotting Founder and CEO Alexa Andrzejewski Virtually Only Woman Onstage at Facebook Developer Conference|last=Women 2.0|date=|work=Forbes|newspaper=|access-date=September 23, 2011|via=}}</ref>
Foodspotting was acquired by [[OpenTable]] in 2013 for $10 million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUS337453604720130129|title=OpenTable will pay $10 million for Foodspotting app|last=|first=|date=January 29, 2013|work=Reuters|access-date=June 17, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> As part of the acquisition, Andrzejewski joined the online reservation platform as a lead user interface designer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/01/29/opentable-will-finally-enter-the-21st-century-with-its-buy-up-of-foodspotting/|title=OpenTable will finally enter the 21st Century with its buy-up of Foodspotting|last=Agarwal|first=Rajat|date=January 29, 2013|work=VentureBeat|access-date=June 17, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>
She was named to [[Inc. (magazine)|''Inc.''<nowiki/>'s]] 2011 list of "[[Inc. 30 under 30|30 Under 30]]" and to [[Forbes|''Forbes''<nowiki/>']] 2012 "[[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]]: Food and Wine" list.<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/special-report/2012/30-under-30/30-under-30_food.html|title=30 Under 30: Food & Wine|date=December 17, 2012|work=Forbes|access-date=June 17, 2018|editor-last=Howard|editor-first=Caroline|language=en|editor2-last=Noer|editor2-first=Michael}}</ref>
