A ''sleeper wall'' is a short [[wall]] used to support [[floor]] [[joist]]s, [[beam and block]] or hollowcore slabs at ground floor. It is constructed in this fashion when a [[suspended slab]] is required due to bearing conditions or ground water presence. Essentially it is a wall in the way that it is constructed but a [http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/sleeper sleeper] in the way that it functions.

Normal construction is of [[brick]] or [[Concrete masonry unit|concrete block]] either in [[stretcher bond]] or [[header stretcher bond]]<!-- Normal construction in what geography?  Is this global? -->

